  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n^2.14.0\n\n### What happened?\n\nWhen I run a local node with Hardhat using `npx hardhat node`, deploy contracts and interact with them, they do not emit any event. The events do not appear on the terminal and I also have a script listening for the events, and It does not get any (I tried already in testnet, and the script gets all the events, but not in the local hardhat node)\r\n\r\nI adjusted the JSON-RPC to url: `HTTP://127.0.0.1:8545` to retrieve the events. Is it something Hardhat does not support?\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/assets/102038261/3957a7d1-77fb-492e-b42f-c00d6e9850c4)\r\n\r\nThanks in advance.\r\n\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\n- Run: `npx hardhat node` .\r\n- Set new URL to deploy the contracts to the local node. (JSON-Provider)\r\n- Deploy contracts.\r\n- Run a server to listen for the events & subscribe to the events.\r\n- Call a Smart contract function that will trigger the events.\r\n- Events are not picked up by the listener. (It works in testnet)\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
